    <innerclass refid="class_tryll_1_1_agent_proxy" prot="public">Tryll::AgentProxy</innerclass>
    <innernamespace refid="namespace_tryll">Tryll</innernamespace>
    <briefdescription>
<para>Client-side handle for a server-hosted Tryll agent. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>An <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_agent_proxy" kindref="compound">Tryll::AgentProxy</ref> is returned by <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_tryll_client_1a464c56ea8abd85c1f3b97a9558b9382a" kindref="member">Tryll::TryllClient::CreateAgent</ref> (or its async twin) and represents one agent running a workflow graph on the server. All turn-driving APIs live on the proxy; the owning <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_tryll_client" kindref="compound">Tryll::TryllClient</ref> handles the underlying session. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
